==== Autonomic Testing

    - Tilt table test: 70-degree head-up tilt for 10 minutes or until symptoms limit continued testing
    - Transcranial Doppler ultrasound: Continuous measurement of middle cerebral artery blood flow velocity
    - Heart rate and blood pressure: Continuous monitoring
    - Outcome: Cerebral blood flow decline magnitude during tilt

